abstract: >-
  A pure-C11 library of SO(3) / SU(2) / O(3) representation-theory
  primitives — spherical harmonics, Wigner-D rotation matrices, Clebsch-
  Gordan coupling, e3nn-style tensor products — with a stable ABI, no
  runtime dependencies beyond libc + libm, and runtime-dispatched NEON
  and AVX2 kernels on the hot paths. Addressed audiences: equivariant-
  neural-network inference engines (NequIP, MACE, Allegro, TENN),
  quantum / spin-system exact diagonalisation, and scientific / graphics
  code needing disciplined rotation mathematics. Algorithms: Jacobi-
  polynomial Wigner-d (stable to j > 80 at machine precision),
  Schulten-Gordon Miller-iterated Wigner 3j / Clebsch-Gordan
  (machine precision to j = 200), sparse Clebsch-Gordan tensor-product
  inner kernel. Also ships a physics substrate — 2D lattices, wallpaper-
  group tables, reduced density matrices, Lanczos — for symmetric
  neural-quantum-state work on the kagome Heisenberg S = 1/2
  ground-state-nature problem.
